The Niger state Sector Command of the Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) has intercepted two overloaded Sharon Vehicles coming into Minna from Kano state. The vehicles were coming into the state on Tuesday being one of the window days. The FRSC immediately notified and invited the Chairman Task Force on COVID-19, Ahmed Matane, including Rative Response Team at Emergency Response Centre( EOC) Minna for further action. Four people including the drivers, two women, and a young boy were inside the intercepted vehicles. The drivers and passengers were all taken to the Quarantine center in Minna as a directive by the State Chairman of COVID-19 Task-Force for questioning and testing. The vehicles were intercepted at about 9.36 am along the Minna – Suleja road. The vehicles are currently impounded at FRSC Office in Minna. Source By Yemi Adeleye Lagos - The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC), RS2 Command, Lagos, says it has recorded nine road crashes with one fatality in Ogun and Lagos States during the lockdown occasioned by Covid-19 pandemic. Mr Samuel Obayemi, the FRSC Zonal Commanding Officer in charge of the two states,… April 17, 2020 In "News" The Niger State government on Wednesday April 15, ordered a trailer filled with over fifty people, to return to Lagos State, where it was reportedly coming from. The Niger state Task Force Team for COVID-19 intercepted the trailer at Gbaganu junction Bida road Minna coming from Lagos with people going… April 16, 2020 In "News" By Stanley Nwanosike Enugu - The Federal Road Safety Corps (FRSC) has commenced massive sensitisation of drivers in motor-parks in Enugu on social distancing in their commercial vehicles to check spread of Coronavirus (COVID-19). News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) recalls that Enugu State Government had earlier directed commercial vehicle drivers… March 28, 2020 In "Metro"